meanings.definition: Matthew Flinders (1774–1814), English navigator and cartographer who charted much of the Australian coastline.
meanings.english_definition: Matthew Flinders (1774–1814), English navigator and cartographer who charted much of the Australian coastline.

meanings.definition: A number of places in Australia named after Matthew Flinders, including Flinders Island and the Flinders Ranges.
meanings.english_definition: A number of places in Australia named after Matthew Flinders, including Flinders Island and the Flinders Ranges.
